<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN PLEADS NOT GUILTY IN VIDEOTAPING OF 
CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A convicted child molester pleaded not guilty Friday to charges that he paid 
children to perform in lewd videotapes. 
</P>
<P>
John Edward Teichrow, 42, faces trial Dec. 20 on five misdemeanor charges 
unrelated to his previous conviction. 
</P>
<P>
He is serving a six-year sentence in a state prison in Chino for molesting 
children in San Bernardino. 
</P>
<P>
Teichrow was transported from the prison to appear in Los Angeles for Friday's 
hearing. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles charges were filed Oct. 30 in connection with the alleged 
videotaping of a 9-year-old boy and a 9-year-old girl at an unidentified 
preschool. Authorities are searching for about 100 other children featured in 
three dozen videotapes found during a search of Teichrow's camper truck, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
He is charged with one count each of possession of child pornography, child 
molestation and loitering near a school, and two counts of committing immoral 
acts in the presence of a child. 
</P>
</TEXT>
