<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILKEN'S SENTENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Judge Wood's sentence for Milken appears to be more of government vengeance 
than justice. Her reasoning that he needs to be made of an example of is quite 
unfair in view of more serious crimes that are going unpunished. Why not apply 
and enforce the same standards of the law against all politicians in this 
country who accept campaign contributions and then influence legislation to 
benefit their donors? Does anyone come to mind? 
</P>
<P>
DON FEIN 
</P>
<P>
Brentwood 
