<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH VISITS U.S. TROOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is this President and his policies for real? Stupid me, I thought our commander 
in chief went to Saudi Arabia Thanksgiving Day to cheer up our troops. Now we 
find that (Nov. 21) Bush's appearance before handpicked troops against a 
custom-painted backdrop -- the whole scenario choreographed by former Las Vegas 
advertising exec Sig Rogich no less -- was designed for only one purpose: To 
pick up Bush's sagging image and to make him look good for the TV cameras. All 
the while, the grunts who stand to die as soon as the shooting starts are 
carefully shunted aside. 
</P>
<P>
BILL LEONG 
</P>
<P>
Bakersfield 
</P>
</TEXT>
