<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Krauthammer's pungent column "Why Go After Hussein? It's as Easy as 
A-B-C" (Column Right, Commentary, Nov. 26) is the most incisive and 
perspicacious argument yet for why Hussein must be harshly dealt with and 
removed from Kuwait, even if it means an all-out attack by military forces. It 
is fervently hoped that President Bush and his advisers read this extremely 
important article. 
</P>
<P>
LANNY R. MIDDINGS 
