<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN SLIPS OFF CLIFF, FALLS 150 FEET TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Calabasas man slipped off a cliff near Topanga Canyon Road and fell 150 feet 
to his death, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
John Emerson Woodson, 45, and his wife, Linda, were driving north on the 
winding road about two miles north of Pacific Coast Highway at 5:30 p.m. 
Thursday when Woodson told his wife to pull to the side, Deputy Britta Rodela 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"He told his wife he had go to the bathroom," Rodela said. "When he didn't 
return 10 minutes later she looked for him and didn't find him." 
</P>
<P>
Linda Woodson drove to a nearby fire station and a search was begun. 
</P>
<P>
A short time later, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Mountain Rescue Team found 
Woodson's body at the bottom of the cliff. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide detectives classified the death as accidental, Rodela said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
