<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / WOMENS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LESLIE SPARKS TROJANS IN VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lisa Leslie, despite foul trouble that kept her on the bench for about half the 
game, scored 16 points and grabbed eight rebounds as the Trojans beat Old 
Dominion, 72-61, in the first round of the Roger White Invitational basketball 
tournament Friday at Northwestern University at Evanston, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
"In the second half, we stuck to our game plan," said Coach Marianne Stanley, 
who had a particular reason to make a good impression. 
</P>
<P>
She came to the Trojans (2-0) after coaching at Old Dominion. 
</P>
<P>
"They had a good game plan in wanting to keep the ball away from Lisa. She 
didn't really get into her game with quick fouls." 
</P>
<P>
Tammy Story had 18 points and four assists for the No. 24-ranked Trojans. 
</P>
<P>
USC plays 14th-ranked Northwestern, a 74-52 winner over Syracuse, in tonight's 
championship game. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA 89, Notre Dame 75 -- Rehema Stephens tied a personal record with 33 
points, 22 in the second half, to lead the Bruins (1-3) in their home opener at 
Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
DeDe Mosman added 20 points and Nicole Anderson had 10 for UCLA, which led 
69-68 with 5:28 to play and went on a 16-2 run over the next four minutes. 
</P>
