<P>
DISPUTE OVER TBS ABORTION PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Rick Du Brow's Nov. 10 column about the protest against Turner Broadcasting 
System's Dec. 7 documentary, "Abortion Denied: Shattering Young Women's Lives": 
</P>
<P>
The tirade by Nellie Gray of the March for Life and Rep. Robert Dornan against 
Ted Turner's TBS channel station for not having a panel discussion after the 
program is typical of the moral and intellectual dishonesty of the 
fundamentalist/far-right movement. 
</P>
<P>
Arguing that Turner is guilty of being one-sided, they conveniently overlook 
how one-sided their own beloved Trinity Broadcasting Network is. 
</P>
<P>
TBN broadcasts 24-hour-a-day, mind-numbing propaganda that exhorts viewers to 
wage Christian warfare against society. It offers virtually no balance. 
</P>
<P>
There is no "other side" for these "bozos," as Turner aptly referred to them. 
Ted, bozos is too kind a characterization. 
</P>
<P>
LARRY SIEGEL 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne 
</P>
