<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Dairy Board Sued: A biotechnology watchdog charged in a lawsuit that 
the National Dairy Board is illegally promoting a growth hormone being used 
experimentally in cows to increase milk production. 
</P>
<P>
Jeremy Rifkin, president of the Washington-based Foundation on Economic Trends, 
has used a variety of legal maneuvers to try to block the use of bovine growth 
hormone on the grounds that it is unsafe. He also petitioned the U.S. Food and 
Drug Administration to "immediately halt any promotion of this product by FDA 
officials and to immediately rescind the use of this product in the marketplace 
until it is approved." Neither the FDA nor the dairy board had a comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
