<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY OFFERS FREE MEASLES VACCINATION FOR PRESCHOOLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA MONROE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Preschoolers can receive their first or second doses of measles vaccine free 
over the next three weeks as the San Diego County Health Services Department 
tries to prevent an epidemic from extending into another year. 
</P>
<P>
The immunizations will be conducted at school sites all over the county, from 
Carlsbad and Fallbrook to Spring Valley and Imperial Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Nearly 960 measles cases, including three deaths, have been reported in San 
Diego County this year. From 1983 to 1988, the number of cases was as low as 
three and as high as 47. A steep rise began last year. 
</P>
<P>
Officials are particularly eager to reach infants and toddlers in the Latino 
community, because the epidemic has disproportionately affected them and their 
brothers and sisters. 
</P>
<P>
In the Sun Belt, an influx of poor, unvaccinated immigrants is generally blamed 
for the increase in measles cases, but federal and state cutbacks in 
free-immunization programs have also contributed to the epidemic. 
</P>
<P>
For the first time, San Diego County clinics will provide second doses of the 
vaccine to 5-year-olds. The added dose is now recommended for all children 
before they enter kindergarten, because, in a few cases, the vaccine fails to 
work the first time around. 
</P>
<P>
Parents who cannot take their children to a special clinic can call the 
county's measles information phone lines for other regular clinic times. The 
numbers are 236-2512 in San Diego and 940-1164 in North County. 
</P>
<P>
Immunization clinics will be held in: 
</P>
<P>
Carlsbad -- Wednesday, Dec. 5, 8-10 a.m. at the Jefferson Elementary School 
health office, 3743 Jefferson St. 
</P>
<P>
Chula Vista -- Friday, Dec. 14, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at the Harborside 
Elementary School health office, 681 Naples St. 
</P>
<P>
Escondido -- Tuesday, Dec. 18, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m., at Lincoln Elementary 
School, Room 32, 1029 N. Broadway. 
</P>
<P>
Fallbrook -- Monday, Dec. 17, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at Fallbrook Street 
Elementary School, 405 W. Fallbrook St. 
</P>
<P>
Imperial Beach -- Thursday, Dec. 13, 11 a.m.-1 p.m. at Central Elementary 
School, 1290 Ebony Ave. 
</P>
<P>
Lakeside -- Wednesday, Dec. 12, 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. in the Lindo Park 
Elementary School auditorium, 12824 Lakeshore Drive. 
</P>
<P>
National City -- Friday, Dec. 7, 10:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. in the Central 
Elementary School auditorium, 933 E Ave. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego -- Tuesday, Dec. 4, 8:30-9:30 a.m. in the Logan Elementary School 
communications room, 2875 Ocean View Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Also, Thursday Dec. 6, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at Brooklyn Elementary School, 
3035 Ash St. 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos -- Wednesday, Dec. 5, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at Paloma Elementary 
School, 660 Camino Magnifico. 
</P>
<P>
Solana Beach -- Tuesday, Dec. 11, 8:30-10:30 a.m. at Solana Vista Elementary 
School, Kiva room, 780 Santa Victoria Ave. 
</P>
<P>
Spring Valley -- Tuesday, Dec. 4, 12:30-2:30 p.m. at the La Presa Elementary 
School stage area, 519 La Presa St. 
</P>
<P>
Vista -- Wednesday, Dec. 19, 10:30 a.m.-12:30 p.m. at Santa Fe Elementary 
School, 600 N. Santa Fe Ave. 
</P>
</TEXT>
