<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-month-old Vista boy was bludgeoned to death and his 34-year-old adoptive 
mother arrested, the San Diego County Sheriff's Department said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Cherie M. Adams, 34, of the 900 block of Lupine Hills in Vista, was arrested 
Thursday night at her home in the death of her adoptive son, Bryan Preston 
Adams, who died Tuesday morning at Tri-City Medical Center, said Sgt. Manny 
Castillo of the sheriff's homicide division. 
</P>
<P>
Adams was held at the County Jail in Vista on a murder charge and one count of 
felony child abuse, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Adams called the Vista Fire Department at 6:58 a.m. Tuesday, saying that she 
had found her son lying unconscious on the floor in his bedroom when she went 
to wake him for breakfast, Castillo said. Sheriff's deputies arrived soon after 
to assist the firefighters, and, after CPR was performed, the child was taken 
to Tri-City where he was pronounced dead at 7:46 a.m., he said. 
</P>
<P>
A coroner's autopsy Wednesday revealed that the toddler had died of internal 
and external injuries caused by blunt force, Castillo said. Further 
investigation by sheriff's homicide and child abuse divisions led to the 
mother's arrest, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Bryan's father, James Adams, a petty officer first class in the Navy, was 
completing an assignment in Honolulu and came home Tuesday, the day of his 
son's death, Castillo said. Bail for Cherie Adams has been set at $250,000, he 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
