<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TUSTIN LIVES UP TO BILLING; LOARA'S WHITLOCK SCORES 49 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 fans packed Tustin High School's gymnasium Friday night to see 
Tustin, The Times' second-ranked basketball team, rout rival Foothill, 88-48. 
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time in 14 years there has been such a blowout in this 
game," Foothill coach Jim Reames said. 
</P>
<P>
"We played an excellent Tustin team that is probably the best since Roger 
Middleton was there." 
</P>
<P>
Tustin used pressure defense to force 14 Foothill turnovers in the first half 
and opened the game with a 15-0 run. 
</P>
<P>
Foothill never recovered from a 27-8 first quarter deficit, and the Knights 
trailed, 62-27, at the end of three quarters. David Beilstein led Tustin with 
24 points, including 20 in the first half along with four three-pointers. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
