</P>
<P>
DAVIS LEADS BANNING RUSH PAST KENNEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE RAATZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tailback Travis Davis scored two touchdowns to lead Banning High to a 20-10 
victory over Kennedy in a City Section 4-A Division quarterfinal football 
playoff game Friday night at Gardena High. 
</P>
<P>
Davis ran for 114 yards in 20 carries for the Pilots (8-3). 
</P>
<P>
Davis also had a 98-yard kickoff return for a touchdown in the third quarter 
and intercepted two passes on defense. 
</P>
<P>
Davis got off to a slow start, gaining only eight yards in his first five 
attempts. But his sixth carry went for 24 yards and a touchdown in the first 
quarter, giving Banning the lead for good at 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy's top rusher, Ontiwaun Carter, was held to 24 yards in 11 carries, 
although Carter did have 52 yards on three receptions. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy (7-5) recorded a first down on its first play from scrimmage as 
quarterback John McMullen threw to Carter for a 22-yard gain, taking the ball 
to the Banning 20-yard line and setting up Keith West's 31-yard field goal. But 
the Cougars didn't get their next first down until the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The Pilots held a 14-3 lead at halftime. Their second touchdown came on a 
two-yard run by fullback Ken McKinley with nine minutes one second left in the 
second quarter and was followed by quarterback Anthony Nicholson's two-point 
conversion run. DAVE RAATZ 
</P>
