<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCTOBER RESTAURANT CLOSURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Department of Health Services has the power to shut down 
food facilities for as long as necessary for the owners to correct conditions 
that pose a danger to the public health. Here is a list of restaurants closed 
during October. 
</P>
<P>
A &amp; R Sandwich Shop -- 145 S. Verdugo Road, Glendale. Closed 10/29 and 
remains closed.* Unsanitary equipment. 
</P>
<P>
Aggie's Restaurant -- 10531 Lower Azusa Road, Temple City. Closed 10/23 to 
10/25. Poor general sanitation. 
</P>
<P>
Anarkali Indian Restaurant -- 7013 Melrose Ave., L.A. Closed 10/1 to 10/2. 
Unsanitary equipment; vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
Chicken on Fire -- 8500 W. Olympic Blvd., Santa Monica. Closed 10/22 to 10/24. 
Vermin infestation; contaminated food. 
</P>
<P>
Church's Burgers -- 9115 S. Normandie Ave., L.A. Closed 10/10 and remains 
closed.* No public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
Continental Taco -- 2355 Peck Road, South El Monte. Closed 10/30 to 10/31. Poor 
general sanitation; no public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
Del Taco -- 11968 E. Garvey Ave., El Monte. Closed 10/3 to 10/4. Unsafe food 
temperatures; poor general sanitation. 
</P>
<P>
Duong Son B-B-Q -- 637 N. Spring St., L.A. Closed 10/25 to 10/30. Poor general 
sanitation; unsanitary equipment; unsafe food temperatures. 
</P>
<P>
El Lucero -- 7312 Pacific Blvd., Walnut Park. Closed 10/25 and remains closed.* 
No public health permit; no plans submitted. 
</P>
<P>
El Serape Restaurant -- 3960 E. Whittier Blvd., L.A. Closed 10/25 to 10/26. No 
potable water supply or no hot water. 
</P>
<P>
Espresso Etc. -- 2425 Colorado Ave., Santa Monica. Closed 10/17 to 10/22. No 
public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
Golden Temple Restaurant -- 7910 W. 3rd St., L.A. Closed 10/10 to 10/11. Vermin 
infestation. 
</P>
<P>
Granny's Donuts -- 8452 Alondra Blvd., Paramount. Closed 10/17 and remains 
closed.* No public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
The Great Wall -- 16842 San Fernando Mission Blvd., Granada Hills. Closed 10/25 
to 10/30. Vermin infestation; sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
H Salt Esquire Fish &amp; Chips -- 12227 Norwalk Blvd., Norwalk. Closed 10/31 
and remains closed.* Sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
Harbor Village Restaurant -- 111 N. Atlantic Blvd., Monterey Park. Closed 10/3 
to 10/5. Poor general sanitation; vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
Indian Cuisine -- 5567 W. Manchester Ave., L.A. Closed 10/11 to 10/12. Vermin 
infestation. 
</P>
<P>
Issendoki -- 333 S. Alameda St., L.A. Closed 10/17 to 10/18. Poor general 
sanitation; unsanitary equipment. 
</P>
<P>
Janitzio Cafe -- 1303 E. 12th St., L.A. Closed 10/22 to 10/25. Poor general 
sanitation; no public health permit; unsafe food temperatures. 
</P>
<P>
Kentucky Fried Chicken -- 12201 Norwalk Blvd., Norwalk. Closed 10/31 and 
remains closed.* Sewage system failure. 
</P>
<P>
Kiki's Coffee Shop -- 3854 S. Crenshaw Blvd., L.A. Closed 10/17 to 10/19. 
Vermin infestation. 
</P>
<P>
La Blanquita Mexican Food -- 2102 N. Long Beach Blvd., Compton. Closed 10/4 to 
10/11. No plans submitted; no public health permit. 
</P>
<P>
Las Vegas Club -- 1812 E. 1st St., L.A. Closed 10/10 to 10/11. Sewage system 
failure. 
</P>
<P>
Las Violetas Bar -- 15537 Lakewood Blvd., Paramount. Closed 10/19 to 10/24. No 
public health permit. 
</P>
