<P>
SCHROEDER TO START AGAINST BRONCOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach Art Shell confirmed Friday that Jay Schroeder will start at quarterback 
Sunday at Denver. 
</P>
<P>
Schroeder, who sprained his left knee in last week's 27-24 loss to the Kansas 
City Chiefs, said he is ready to play. 
</P>
<P>
Shell said he would wait until today to decide whether to activate quarterback 
Steve Beuerlein for the first time this season. 
</P>
<P>
Although the Broncos have lost four consecutive games, their longest losing 
streak since 1972 and the longest losing streak by a Dan Reeves-coached team, 
quarterback John Elway said Denver isn't giving up. 
</P>
<P>
"We're not quitting yet," Elway said. "We're going to hang in there and keep 
going. That's all we can say." CHRIS BAKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
