<P>
COMEDY BENEFIT FOR THE FORCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNNE HEFFLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fourth annual "A-PAC-A-LAFS-NOW" comedy benefit, with headliners Roseanne 
Barr and Tom Arnold, will be heard by forces in the Middle East. KLSX Radio is 
taping the event on Monday at the Improvisation in Santa Monica; it will be 
broadcast internationally by Armed Forces Radio at a later date via satellite. 
</P>
<P>
Joining Barr and Arnold in performance will be Jim Carrey, Michael Colyar, 
Tommy Davidson, Rick Duccomun and David Alan Grier of "In Living Color," 
comedians Mike Binder and Blake Clark (creator of the event), "Police 
Academy's" Michael Winslow and surprise guests. 
</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the show, which is open to the public, will go to the Vietnam 
Veterans Aid Foundation. Tickets are $25 for the show; $50 for show and 
reception. Information: (800) 366-VVAF. LYNNE HEFFLEY 
</P>
