SPORTS ON WEEKEND TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rams and Raiders, along with the Clippers, Lakers and UCLA, USC and 
Pepperdine basketball teams, will be among the weekend viewing choices. 
</P>
<P>
The Lakers put their five-game winning streak on the line against the Phoenix 
Suns tonight (6:30 p.m., Channels 9, 51 and 63). 
</P>
<P>
The Clippers take on the defensive-minded Minnesota Timberwolves at 6 p.m. 
Sunday on Prime Ticket. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday's pro football kicks off at 10 a.m. when the Rams (4-7) visit the 
Cleveland Browns (2-9) (Channels 2 and 8). Channels 4 and 36 counter with a 
Miami Dolphins-Washington Redskins game at 10 a.m. The Raiders will seek to 
avoid losing for the fourth time in five games when they visit AFC West rival 
Denver Broncos (1 p.m., Channels 4, 36 and 39). ESPN's 5 p.m. game matches the 
Minnesota Vikings (5-6), winners of four consecutive games, and the Green Bay 
Packers (6-5). 
</P>
<P>
In college basketball, No. 12 UCLA hosts Loyola Marymount Sunday, with Prime 
Ticket's delayed broadcast beginning at 11:30 p.m. In another Prime Ticket 
delayed broadcast, USC plays Miami (Fla.) at 2 p.m. today. Prime Ticket also 
has a live Pepperdine-DePaul telecast at 5 p.m. today. 
</P>
