terminate his contract on Dec. 30. Vice Supt. William Brown was named acting 
superintendent. The superintendent narrowly escaped firing in July, when the 
board decided to keep him on until his contract expired at the end of this 
school year. The school system has been plagued by one of the highest dropout 
rates in the nation, a declining enrollment and a shortage of funds. 
